@chessy019 wrote:

Etheir the server is:
1.Its actaully down
2.Too many people are online and you cannot get in
3.You havent downloaded the right java or the latest java.
4.Check to make sure you’re spelling everything right like the port & IP. If the server requires Hamachi, Download it & install it. Make sure when you are connected to the Hamachi server that you are fully connected to the server owner (green glowing dot next to the name or a blue glowing arrow.)

   Hope this helps!

item.title: Aaaaaaaaaahhhhhhhhhhh! omfg!
item.dc:creator: @Paradise_God Paradise God
item.description:
@Paradise_God wrote:

[quote=“breaking the bridge, post:8, topic:69979”]Ok, first you could type what your quesiton is in the title

Probably one of the following…

[ul][li]Server Is Down[/li]
[li]You Have No Internet Connection[/li]
[li]You Don’t Have The Latest Java? Probably Not The Problem But Can Be Found Here[/li][/ul]

~Glad To Help Anyone, Also If You Need Any More Help, Visit My Help Topic Which Can Be Found Here~[/quote]
That was basically spam…

But anyway, when you compile your server, then run your server…

When the box comes up after you’ve clicked runserver, it should say, Server running on 0.0.0[Port here]

Enter that port, (Proabaly about 4-5 numbers)
Enter the IP, (If you running by Hamachi, Make sure you have an Hamachi network, and the IP to YOUR server is the bigt number’s at the top of your hamachi).

Log in. then make your self Admin, or Owner Admin.
